snippet.textDisplay:
You know what's great about these places and this show?
This show puts these places in public eye, thus bringing all of it's problems to the attention of various inspector officials and such.
Meaning that if they didn't get their shit together, they would be closed down and no longer a danger to public health.
I noticed the pattern with these episodes. Shortly after it gets aired, if the places did not get better. They closed down.
So really it boils down to this
If your business is on Kitchen Nightmares or Hotel Hell, you better get your shit straight, because you don't have long before you get invaded by inspectors and other sorts of officials looking to shut your ass down.
